trans-unit.source: Returns an enumerator that can iterate through the collection.
trans-unit.target: Retorna um enumerador que pode iterar pela coleção.

trans-unit.source: Enumerators only allow reading the data in the collection.
trans-unit.target: Enumeradores permitem apenas ler os dados na coleção.

trans-unit.source: Enumerators cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: Enumeradores não podem ser usados para modificar a coleção subjacente.

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first item in the collection.
trans-unit.target: Inicialmente, o enumerador está posicionado antes do primeiro item na coleção.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>também traz o enumerador de volta para essa posição.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>

trans-unit.source: At this position, calling <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.
trans-unit.target: AT isso posicionar, chamando <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>lança uma exceção.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first item of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Portanto, você deve chamar <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>para avançar o enumerador para o primeiro item da coleção antes de ler o valor de <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>Retorna o mesmo objeto até que o <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>ou <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>é chamado.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A></xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the next item.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>define <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>para o próximo item.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A></xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: After the end of the collection is passed, the enumerator is positioned after the last item in the collection, and calling <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: Após o final da coleção for passado, o enumerador está posicionado após o último item na coleção e chamada <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>retorna `false`.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, calling <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.
trans-unit.target: Se a última chamada <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>retornado `false`, chamar <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>lança uma exceção.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the first item of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Para definir <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>como o primeiro item da coleção novamente, você pode chamar <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>seguido pelo <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: Um enumerador permanece válido desde que a coleção permaneça inalterada.

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying or deleting items, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and the next call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> throws an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.
trans-unit.target: Se forem feitas alterações à coleção, como adicionar, modificar ou excluir itens, o enumerador será invalidado irrecuperavelmente e a próxima chamada ou <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>gera um <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the collection is modified between <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> will return the item that it is set to, even if the enumerator is already invalidated.
trans-unit.target: Se a coleção é modificada entre <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>e <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>retornará o item que está definido como, mesmo se o enumerador já é invalidado.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: O enumerador não tem acesso exclusivo à coleção; Portanto, enumerando através de uma coleção intrinsecamente não é um procedimento de thread-safe.

trans-unit.source: Even when a collection is synchronized, other threads could still modify the collection, which causes the enumerator to throw an exception.
trans-unit.target: Mesmo quando uma coleção é sincronizada, outros threads ainda podem modificar a coleção, o que faz com que o enumerador lançar uma exceção.

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can either lock the collection during the entire enumeration or catch the exceptions resulting from changes made by other threads.
trans-unit.target: Para garantir a segurança de thread durante a enumeração, você pode bloquear a coleção durante toda a enumeração ou capture as exceções resultante de alterações feitas por outros threads.

trans-unit.source: Searches for the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextEffect"></xref> and returns the zero-based index of the first occurrence within the entire collection.
trans-unit.target: Procura especificado <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextEffect"> </xref> e retorna o índice baseado em zero da primeira ocorrência na coleção inteira.

trans-unit.source: The collection is searched forward starting at the first key frame and ending at the last key frame.
trans-unit.target: A coleção é pesquisada forward iniciando no primeiro quadro chave e terminando no último quadro chave.

trans-unit.source: This method performs a linear search; therefore, the average execution time is proportional to <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ColorKeyFrameCollection.Count%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Esse método executa uma pesquisa linear; Portanto, o tempo médio de execução é proporcional ao <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ColorKeyFrameCollection.Count%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ColorKeyFrameCollection.Count%2A>

trans-unit.source: That is, this method is an O(*n*) operation, where *n* is <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ColorKeyFrameCollection.Count%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Ou seja, esse método é um O (*n*) operação, onde *n* é <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ColorKeyFrameCollection.Count%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ColorKeyFrameCollection.Count%2A>
